gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Jazz 132, Lakers 125
gameRecap.excerpt: The Jazz defeated the Lakers, 132-125, as they in their fifth straight game and improve to 21-20 on the year. Lauri Markkanen led the Jazz with 29 points, 10 rebounds, and five assists as Collin Sexton (27 points, five assists) and Jordan Clarkson (21 points) totaled 48 points. D'Angelo Russell led the Lakers with a season-high 39 points, along with eight assists as Anthony Davis tallied his second career triple-double (15 points, 15 rebounds, career-high 11 assists, and four blocks). The Lakers move to 19-21.
